node.title: Cairns, Mission beach on alert as woman COVID-19 positive aftter travelling through Queensland
node.alt: Annastacia Palaszczuk speaks at a press conference in Brisbane.
node.description: Queensland issues contact tracing alerts for locations in Cairns and Mission Beach after a person tested positive for COVID-19 in the Northern Territory after transiting through the region.
node.content:
["Queensland Health has issued contact tracing alerts for locations in Cairns and Mission Beach after a person tested positive for COVID-19\u00a0in the Northern Territory after transiting through the region.", "NT authorities on Sunday said the woman, who spent time in Victoria before flying to Cairns from Adelaide and then\u00a0to Darwin, was the primary infection case sparking a lockout in parts of the Top End.", "Queensland Health said she was infectious in the Queensland community before leaving the state.", "There are exposure alerts for a Jetstar flight from Adelaide to Cairns that left at 6am\u00a0on Monday, October 25, as well as Gate 20 at the Cairns Domestic Airport.", "There's an alert for Gate 21 at the airport from midday on Friday, October 29.", "There are several exposure alerts for shops, including Cotton On and Kmart in the Cairns Central Shopping Centre that Friday morning, and Woolworths at Mission Beach on the afternoon of Wednesday, October 27.", "All the alerts are for casual or low-risk contacts but authorities advise anyone in the Cairns region with any symptoms\u00a0to get tested.", "There is also\u00a0a small cluster in the Queensland border town of Goondiwindi, with 5,826 tests done in the past 24 hours.\u00a0", "
Eighty per cent first dose target close by
", "Premier Annastacia Palaszczuk said the state looked\u00a0set to hit 80 per cent\u00a0of the eligible population over 16 years with a first dose of a COVID-19 vaccine by Tuesday.", "About 14,000 vaccines were administered by Queensland Health on Saturday.", "Speaking from a hardware store in the Brisbane suburb of Stafford, Ms Palaszczuk said more than 2,000 vaccines were administered through hardware stores on Saturday.", "\"More than 50 per cent were first doses, and what we're seeing on the north side of Brisbane, is that they're young people, so that's fantastic,\" she said.", "\"That's the cohort we're concerned about at the moment.\"", "Ms Palaszczuk said the state's first dose rate was now at 79\u00a0per cent.", "Almost 67 per cent of eligible Queenslanders over 16 years old are now fully vaccinated.\u00a0", "Acting Chief Health Officer Peter Aitken said contact tracing details for the\u00a0new cases in quarantine were being worked through.", "", "
Queensland\u00a0Acting Chief Health Officer Dr Peter Aitken\u00a0speaks at a press conference in Brisbane on November 7, 2021.\u00a0(ABC News: Tobias Jurss-Lewis)
", "Dr Aitken said the two international travellers who tested positive had travelled from the Ukraine via Dubai.", "Authorities have now confirmed a fourth case connected to the Goondiwindi cluster announced yesterday, was not infectious in the community.", "
'Cautiously optimistic'
", "Ms Palaszczuk said the state was \"absolutely\" on track to hit its predicted date for 80 per cent fully vaccinated.", "Dr Aitken said they were feeling \"cautiously optimistic\" about the Goondiwindi cluster.", "\"It's early days still, we haven't got through a full incubation period,\" he said.", "\"At this stage, the fact there's been no new cases \u2014 no community transmission \u2014 the only cases have been identified close contacts is really positive news.", "\"I think its testament again to the Goondiwindi community with their high vaccination rates.", "\"Optimistic, hopeful, not quite there.\"", "", "
